  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safecast - Japan Radiation Monitoring</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safecast is a global project working to empower people with data, primarily by mapping radiation levels and building a sensor network, enabling people to both contribute and freely use the data collected. After the 3/11 earthquake and resulting nuclear situation at Fukushima Diachi it became clear that people wanted more data than what was available. Safecast has been building a radiation sensor network comprised of static and mobile sensors actively being deployed around Japan.</narrative>
  </description>
